# Cypress Automation
The Cypress automation suite includes test scripts written in JavaScript using the Cypress testing framework. These scripts simulate user interactions with the HR Management System, performing end-to-end tests, API testing, UI testing, and other scenarios to validate the system's functionalities.

# Features Covered:
Login Functionality: Authentication and access control.
Employee Management: Adding, editing, deleting employee profiles.
Leave Management: Testing leave request submissions, approvals, and rejections.
Payroll Management: Validating salary calculations, deductions, and bonuses.
Performance Evaluations: Testing performance review functionalities.
API Testing: Verifying backend functionalities through API requests.
Various Scenarios: Error handling, input validations, and edge cases.

# Getting Started

Prerequisites
Node.js installed on your machine
Clone this repository
Installing Cypress
To run the Cypress automation scripts locally:

1. Install Cypress globally or locally in the project:

npm install cypress --save-dev

2. Clone this repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/marcusautomatic/orange_automation

Running Tests
To run Cypress tests:

# Open Cypress:


npx cypress open
Select a test file to run or execute all tests.

# Contributions
Contributions and improvements to the test suite are welcome! Fork the repository, make changes, and create a pull request.
